The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 06 December is 118,418 (13,648.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 01 December, there were 5,692 new confirmed cases (656.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 24 November, there were 5,612 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 1% (80 extra cases).
